                     <interp inst="t18300916-31-person370" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am solicitor to the Society of the Middle Temple - the property is vested in Mr. 
               <persName id="t18300916-31-person371">
                  Robert 
                  Malkew Casberd
               <interp inst="t18300916-31-person371" type="surname" value="Malkew Casberd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-31-person371" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-31-person371" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and two others.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I told the witness the person had gone to get a pint of beer at the corner public-house; I was coming through the Temple, and a person asked me if I wanted a job, and he employed me to carry this to Seven-dials - when we got to the corner he said he would give me a drop of beer.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300916-31-verdict173" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-31-verdict173" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30. - <rs id="t18300916-31-punish174" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-31-punish174" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-31-defend363 t18300916-31-punish174"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
